## Rules

### TEST-001: pytest Fixtures
severity: ERROR
scope: all Python test files
rule: Tests MUST use pytest fixtures for setup and teardown. Global test state is prohibited. Tests that modify the filesystem MUST use `tmp_path`. Test class names MUST start with `Test`.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80, max_test_file_lines=300
example_correct: |
  def test_process_order(tmp_path: Path) -> None:
      project = tmp_path / "myapp"
      ...
example_incorrect: |
  PROJECT_DIR = Path("/tmp/shared")  # shared mutable — prohibited

### TEST-002: No Bare Exceptions
severity: ERROR
scope: all test files
rule: Tests MUST use `pytest.raises(SpecificException)` to assert exceptions. Catching bare `Exception` in tests is prohibited. Tests MUST assert specific error messages where applicable.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80
example_correct: |
  with pytest.raises(ValueError, match="invalid domain"):
      PromptLoader(project_root).load_for_feature("x")
example_incorrect: |
  try:
      func()
  except Exception:
      pass  # swallowing exception — prohibited
